            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>gochujang paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) with the <strong>soy sauce</strong> and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>cold</strong> <strong>water </strong>in a small bowl and mix well – this is your <strong>gochujang mixture</strong></p><p>Once the spring onions are soft, add the <strong>drained potatoes</strong> and <strong>gochujang mixture </strong>to the pan and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to brown</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1629798948472-x200.jpg",
